diff --git a/blog/fat-freeze-realistic-expectations.html b/blog/fat-freeze-realistic-expectations.html
index fcf0d9d..5527db3 100644
--- a/blog/fat-freeze-realistic-expectations.html
+++ b/blog/fat-freeze-realistic-expectations.html
@@ -206,7 +206,7 @@
 <p>The single biggest misconception about fat freeze (cryolipolysis) is that it's a weight-loss treatment. It's not. It's a body-contouring treatment for people already close to their goal weight. Let's be honest about what it does and doesn't deliver.</p>
 
 <h2>What Fat Freeze Actually Does</h2>
-<p>It permanently kills fat cells in a specific, treated area. The body clears those cells over 8–12 weeks. Result: a visible reduction in the treated fat pocket — usually 20–25% per session per area.</p>
+<p>It permanently kills fat cells in a specific, treated area — once destroyed, they don't regenerate, a selective cold-injury effect first demonstrated in the pre-clinical research behind cryolipolysis (Manstein et al., 2008). The body clears those cells over 8–12 weeks. Result: a visible reduction in the treated fat pocket — published trial data put the average fat-layer thickness reduction from a single session at around 20% on ultrasound measurement, though the exact figure varies by treatment area and your starting fat thickness (Boey &amp; Wasilenchuk, 2014).</p>
 
 <h2>What It Doesn't Do</h2>
 <p>It doesn't affect fat elsewhere in your body. It doesn't change your weight significantly (you might lose 1–2 kg from a treated area). It doesn't improve health markers like cholesterol or diabetes risk. It doesn't tighten loose skin.</p>
@@ -224,14 +224,24 @@
 <p>Combining fat freeze with continued healthy eating and moderate exercise gives the best long-term results. The fat cells removed by fat freeze don't come back, but remaining fat cells can enlarge if you gain weight.</p>
 
 <h2>Realistic Timeline</h2>
-<p>Book your session. Wait 8–12 weeks. Peak results usually visible at 3 months. You may need a second session on the same area if fat pocket is thick. Track with photos, not scales — scale weight barely changes.</p>
+<p>Book your session. Wait 8–12 weeks — the follow-up window used in the pivotal studies that supported cryolipolysis's FDA clearances (Zelickson et al., 2015). Peak results usually visible at 3 months. You may need a second session on the same area if fat pocket is thick. Track with photos, not scales — scale weight barely changes.</p>
 
 <h2>Fat Freeze vs Alternatives</h2>
-<p>Compared to liposuction: fat freeze is non-invasive, no downtime, but more limited in one-session results. Compared to injection lipolysis (Kybella): fat freeze is cheaper and better for larger areas. See our <a href="/compare/fat-freeze-vs-liposuction">detailed comparison</a>.</p>
+<p>Compared to liposuction: fat freeze is non-invasive, no downtime, but more limited in one-session results. Compared to injection lipolysis (Kybella): fat freeze is generally cheaper and better suited to larger areas. See our <a href="/compare/fat-freeze-vs-liposuction">detailed comparison</a>.</p>
 
 
         </div>
 
+        <section class="blog-post__sources" style="margin-top:2.5rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border, #D4CBC0);">
