diff --git a/blog/monsoon-skincare-mumbai.html b/blog/monsoon-skincare-mumbai.html
index 3ae4a76..aea3a3b 100644
--- a/blog/monsoon-skincare-mumbai.html
+++ b/blog/monsoon-skincare-mumbai.html
@@ -206,16 +206,16 @@
 <p>Mumbai monsoon is beautiful. It's also the worst season for skin. Humidity, sweat, changing weather, and reduced sun exposure combine to create unique challenges. Here's what I tell my patients every June.</p>
 
 <h2>The Monsoon Skin Problems</h2>
-<p>Increased breakouts (humid air + sweat + oily skin), fungal infections (in body folds), scalp itchiness/dandruff, dull skin (less sun = less natural vitamin D), and paradoxically, dry patches (humidity + AC combo).</p>
+<p>Increased breakouts (humid air + sweat + oily skin) — a cross-sectional study of acne patients in tropical Delhi found that both temperature and humidity correlated significantly with seasonal flares, with aggravation most commonly reported in the summer and rainy months (Narang et al., 2018). Also common: fungal infections (in body folds), scalp itchiness/dandruff, dull skin (less sun = less natural vitamin D), and paradoxically, dry patches (humidity + AC combo).</p>
 
 <h2>Prioritise Cleansing</h2>
-<p>Wash your face 2–3 times a day with a gentle cleanser — more if you're sweating a lot. Salicylic acid-based cleansers help oily/acne-prone skin. Don't over-scrub; that damages the skin barrier and worsens breakouts.</p>
+<p>Wash your face 2–3 times a day with a gentle cleanser — more if you're sweating a lot. Salicylic acid-based cleansers help oily, acne-prone skin; in professional-strength peel form, salicylic acid was among the more effective chemical-peel options for acne in a recent systematic review of procedural therapies (Pour Mohammad et al., 2025), though at far higher concentrations than a daily cleanser. Don't over-scrub; that damages the skin barrier and worsens breakouts.</p>
 
 <h2>Fight the Fungus</h2>
-<p>Body folds (underboob, groin, underarms) are prime real estate for fungal infections during monsoon. Keep them dry, use antifungal dusting powders after showers, and change out of wet clothes immediately. See a dermatologist for stubborn fungal infections.</p>
+<p>Body folds (underboob, groin, underarms) are prime real estate for fungal infections during monsoon. Hot, humid conditions are a documented risk factor for yeast and fungal folliculitis outbreaks, as seen in a reported case series among residents of a non-air-conditioned, humid facility (Jalalat et al., 2014). Keep them dry, use antifungal dusting powders after showers, and change out of wet clothes immediately. See a dermatologist for stubborn fungal infections.</p>
 
 <h2>Don't Skip Sunscreen</h2>
-<p>Common mistake. Even when it's cloudy, UV rays penetrate. Use a lightweight, non-comedogenic SPF 50+. Gel formulations work well for oily skin.</p>
+<p>Common mistake. Even when it's cloudy, UV rays still reach the skin — measurements of ambient UV in shaded and unshaded settings found that increasing cloud cover actually reduces the protective benefit of shade, because more radiation arrives as scattered, diffuse light rather than direct sun (Moise &amp; Aynsley, 1999). Use a lightweight, non-comedogenic SPF 50+. Gel formulations work well for oily skin.</p>
 
 <h2>Treatments to Prioritise in Monsoon</h2>
 <p>Monsoon is actually a great time to start <a href="/services/laser-hair-removal-mumbai">laser hair removal</a> — sun exposure is naturally lower. Also excellent for pigmentation treatments (<a href="/services/carbon-laser-facial">Carbon Facial</a>, peels) because your sun exposure is reduced.</p>
