@@ -215,13 +215,13 @@
 <p>Your dermatologist will look at: skin laxity (loose skin), fat distribution (where it's stubborn), diastasis recti (abdominal separation), stretch marks (fresh red vs old white), and cellulite. Every plan is personalised based on this.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 2: Address Fat and Skin</h2>
-<p><a href="/services/fat-freeze">Fat Freeze</a> for persistent belly and love-handle pockets. <a href="/services/jordi-shape">Jordi Shape</a> for cellulite, skin firming, and lymphatic drainage. Discuss timing with your dermatologist if you're breastfeeding — safety data specific to lactation is limited, so this is decided case-by-case rather than assumed.</p>
+<p><a href="/services/fat-freeze">Fat Freeze</a> for persistent belly and love-handle pockets — a prospective study of cryolipolysis on the abdomen found meaningful, sustained reductions in fat-layer thickness and circumference at both 3 and 6 months post-treatment, with no major adverse events reported (Coiante et al., 2023). <a href="/services/jordi-shape">Jordi Shape</a> for cellulite, skin firming, and lymphatic drainage. Discuss timing with your dermatologist if you're breastfeeding — safety data specific to lactation is limited, so this is decided case-by-case rather than assumed.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 3: Rebuild Core Strength</h2>
-<p><a href="/services/hifem-body-toning">HIFEM Body Toning</a> is a game-changer for post-pregnancy core weakness and diastasis recti. It stimulates muscle contractions equivalent to thousands of crunches. 4 sessions per area over 2 weeks.</p>
+<p><a href="/services/hifem-body-toning">HIFEM Body Toning</a> is a game-changer for post-pregnancy core weakness and diastasis recti. MRI-based studies of HIFEM (the technology behind this treatment) have documented measurable increases in rectus abdominis muscle thickness alongside a reduction in abdominal muscle separation after a course of sessions (Kinney &amp; Lozanova, 2018), with one-year follow-up imaging suggesting those muscle and diastasis changes hold up over time (Kinney &amp; Kent, 2020). Typical protocol: 4 sessions per area over 2 weeks.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 4: Stretch Marks</h2>
-<p>Fresh red/purple stretch marks respond faster than old white ones. <a href="/services/mnrf">MNRF (Micro-Needling RF)</a> is the best treatment — 4–6 sessions over 4–6 months, with 40–60% visible improvement expected. Not 100% removal, but significantly less noticeable.</p>
+<p>Fresh red/purple stretch marks respond faster than old white ones. <a href="/services/mnrf">MNRF (Micro-Needling RF)</a> is among the better-evidenced options — systematic reviews and meta-analyses of microneedling-based treatments for stretch marks report consistent, meaningful improvement in the majority of patients across 4–6 sessions over 4–6 months (Sun et al., 2024). Results vary by individual and by how old the stretch marks are; expect visible fading rather than complete disappearance, which is uncommon.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 5: Skin Recovery</h2>
 <p>Pregnancy affects facial skin too — melasma, pigmentation, dullness. See our <a href="/concerns/pigmentation-melasma">pigmentation guide</a> for those concerns. Face and body plans run in parallel.</p>
