diff --git a/blog/when-indian-women-start-anti-ageing.html b/blog/when-indian-women-start-anti-ageing.html
index 835ce71..bb32f8d 100644
--- a/blog/when-indian-women-start-anti-ageing.html
+++ b/blog/when-indian-women-start-anti-ageing.html
@@ -206,10 +206,10 @@
 <p>One question I hear often: "Am I too young to start anti-ageing treatments?" Or "Am I too late?" The answer depends on your skin, genetics, and lifestyle — not just age. Here's a decade-by-decade guide for Indian women.</p>
 
 <h2>The 20s: Prevention Foundation</h2>
-<p>Your 20s are for prevention, not correction. Focus on: daily SPF 50+ (this alone prevents 80% of visible ageing), retinol at night (start low, build slowly), vitamin C serum in the morning, and adequate sleep and hydration. In-clinic: monthly <a href="/services/hydra-facial">Hydra Facial</a> for hydration, quarterly light peels for texture. Don't start injectables or aggressive lasers unless you have a specific concern.</p>
+<p>Your 20s are for prevention, not correction. Focus on: daily SPF 50+ — sun protection is the single most evidence-backed anti-ageing habit, and in a 4.5-year randomised controlled trial, adults who used sunscreen daily showed 24% less visible photoageing than those who applied it only at their own discretion (Hughes et al., 2013); retinol at night, starting low (around 0.1%) and building slowly — even low-dose retinol has been shown in a placebo-controlled study to improve fine lines and skin tone without significant irritation (Bellemère et al., 2009); vitamin C serum in the morning; and adequate sleep and hydration. In-clinic: monthly <a href="/services/hydra-facial">Hydra Facial</a> for hydration, quarterly light peels for texture. Don't start injectables or aggressive lasers unless you have a specific concern.</p>
 
 <h2>The 30s: Early Correction</h2>
-<p>Collagen production drops ~1% per year after 25 — you'll start noticing subtle changes. Fine lines around eyes and mouth. Slight loss of jawline definition. Uneven texture. Start: consistent <a href="/services/mnrf">MNRF</a> for collagen (annual course), <a href="/services/chemical-peel">quarterly peels</a> for texture and pigment, targeted retinoid strength (0.5–1%), preventive Botox for expressive lines (if desired). Skip: aggressive fillers, unnecessary "prejuvenation" trends.</p>
+<p>Collagen production declines measurably with age — foundational dermal biopsy research established that skin collagen content falls fairly steadily through adulthood (Shuster et al., 1975), which is where the commonly cited estimate of roughly 1% collagen loss per year comes from. In practice, you'll start noticing subtle changes. Fine lines around eyes and mouth. Slight loss of jawline definition. Uneven texture. Start: consistent <a href="/services/mnrf">MNRF</a> for collagen (annual course), <a href="/services/chemical-peel">quarterly peels</a> for texture and pigment, targeted retinoid strength (0.5–1%), preventive Botox for expressive lines (if desired). Skip: aggressive fillers, unnecessary "prejuvenation" trends.</p>
 
 <h2>The 40s: Active Rejuvenation</h2>
 <p>The decade of visible ageing accelerates: jawline sagging, deeper lines, volume loss, more pigment. This is when non-invasive lifting becomes valuable. Start: <a href="/services/hifu-face-lift">HIFU</a> for jawline and jowl definition, MNRF regularly, targeted fillers for tear troughs or cheek volume (if needed), professional-grade home care (prescription retinol, brightening actives). Consider: annual maintenance HIFU, biannual MNRF courses.</p>
